Component authoring rules (renderer)

- Prefer explicit props and return types over React.FC.
  - Do: `type Props = {}; const Component = ({}: Props): React.JSX.Element => { ... }`
  - Avoid: `const Component: React.FC<Props> = (props) => { ... }`
  - Rationale: prevents implicit children, simplifies generics, and avoids redundant typing with TS 5 + React 19.

- Only accept `children` when needed.
  - Do: `type Props = { children: React.ReactNode }` explicitly.

- Use English-only identifiers and comments. Keep files in kebab-case.

- Ensure `.app-region-drag`/`.app-region-no-drag` are used on window chrome to avoid drag conflicts.

